While engaged in its conflict with Russia, Ukraine has recently launched a massive anti-corruption campaign, with a number of senior officials being dismissed. Is victory for Ukraine possible as it deals with both external threats and internal problems? What are the realistic scenarios to resolve the crisis? In this Dialogue Special, Ukraine Crisis: One Year On, the guests are Petro Burkovskiy, Executive Director of the Democratic Initiatives Foundation and Vladimir Golstein, Chair of the Department of Slavic Studies at Brown University.